LineNo: 10476743,

Narrator: A few weeks had passed since the at...
en


A few weeks had passed since the attack in Zille.

LineNo: 10476845,

Narrator: I called Lucita, Hugo, Titus and Vi...
en


I called Lucita, Hugo, Titus and Vina to my council chambers for a security update.

LineNo: 10477225,

Narrator: I called Lucita, Hugo and Titus to...
en


I called Lucita, Hugo and Titus to my council chambers for a security update.

LineNo: 10477327,

Narrator: Titus insisted on sweeping the room...
en


Titus insisted on sweeping the room before Vina and I sat down. Hugo was next to arrive, early as usual.

LineNo: 10477429,

Narrator: Titus insisted on sweeping the room...
en


Titus insisted on sweeping the room before I sat down. Hugo was next to arrive, early as usual.

LineNo: 10477531,

Hugo Toras: Your Majesty. How are you faring?
en


"Your Majesty. How are you faring?"

LineNo: 10477657,

Player_Romus: I'm still in shock. How was such a...
en


"I'm still in shock. How was such an attack allowed to take place in the King's presence?"

LineNo: 10477759,

Player_Romus: I'm just fine. It's the Wehzek vic...
en


"I'm just fine. It's the Wehzek victims of the bombing I'm concerned about."

LineNo: 10477861,

Player_Romus: I'm doing all right. So is Mother,...
en


"I'm doing all right. So is Mother, in case you cared."

LineNo: 10477963,

Player_Romus: I'm worried about Wehlen's reactio...
en


"I'm worried about Wehlen's reaction. Smolak hasn't even made a public statement yet."

LineNo: 10478065,

Hugo Toras: Perhaps no news is good news in th...
en


"Perhaps no news is good news in this case."

LineNo: 10478167,

Hugo Toras: I can only hope Duchess Azaro will...
en


"I can only hope Duchess Azaro will enlighten us on that matter."

LineNo: 10478269,

Hugo Toras: It was God's will that you survive...
en


"It was God's will that you survived. Losing two kings within a year would have been catastrophic for this country."

LineNo: 10478371,

Hugo Toras: Of course the Queen Mother's safet...
en


"Of course the Queen Mother's safety is of the utmost importance to me. But losing two kings in a matter of months would have been catastrophic."

LineNo: 10478473,

Player_Romus: At ease, Duchess Azaro.
en


"At ease, Duchess Azaro."

LineNo: 10478575,

Player_Romus: I need a status report. Now.
en


"I need a status report. Now."

LineNo: 10478677,

Player_Romus: We're not all gentlemen. Do not fo...
en


"We're not all gentlemen. Do not forget the presence of the princess."

LineNo: 10478779,

Player_Romus: Thank you for joining us, Duchess...
en


"Thank you for joining us, Duchess Azaro. Can you update us on the Zille situation?"

LineNo: 10478881,

Lucita Azaro: Certainly, Your Majesty.
en


"Certainly, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10478983,

Lucita Azaro: Thank you, Your Majesty.
en


"Thank you, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10479085,

Narrator: Lucita sat and flipped open a dossi...
en


Lucita sat and flipped open a dossier.

LineNo: 10479187,

Narrator: Still standing, she picked a dossie...
en


Still standing, she picked a dossier up off the table and flipped it open.

LineNo: 10479289,

Lucita Azaro: I'll reiterate what we already kno...
en


"I'll reiterate what we already know."

LineNo: 10479391,

Lucita Azaro: At 1605 hours on December 8, 1950,...
en


"At 1605 hours on December 8, 1950, an explosive object detonated in Smolak Square in the city of Zille. It had been planted beneath grandstands that were set up that morning."

LineNo: 10479493,

Lucita Azaro: Seated in those stands were a mix...
en


"Seated in those stands were a mix of civilians and political figures who had been invited to the Friendship Day event, all of Wehzek heritage."

LineNo: 10479595,

Lucita Azaro: The most recent casualty report st...
en


"The most recent casualty report states that three civilians were killed in the blast. Of the 14 injured, all are now in stable condition."

LineNo: 10479721,

Player_Romus: Don't forget that right before the...
en


"Don't forget that right before the attack, someone screamed 'For the King.'"

LineNo: 10479823,

Player_Romus: Yes, yes, we know all that. What's...
en


"Yes, yes, we know all that. What's new?"

LineNo: 10479925,

Player_Romus: Was anyone important among the dea...
en


"Was anyone important among the dead?"

LineNo: 10480027,

Player_Romus: Thank God. From what I saw, it cou...
en


"Thank God. From what I saw, it could have been much worse."

LineNo: 10480129,

Lucita Azaro: No, the most prominent Wehzek atte...
en


"No, the most prominent Wehzek attendees all made it out unharmed. Wehlen's guards saw to that."

LineNo: 10480231,

Lucita Azaro: It's not good for us regardless.
en


"It's not good for us regardless."

LineNo: 10480333,

Lucita Azaro: I was getting to that.
en


"I was getting to that."

LineNo: 10480435,

Lucita Azaro: I haven't forgotten. Nor has Wehle...
en


"I haven't forgotten. Nor has Wehlen."

LineNo: 10480537,

Narrator: She turned a page.
en


She turned a page.

LineNo: 10480639,

Lucita Azaro: Based on the scant evidence availa...
en


"Based on the scant evidence available, Wehlen's intelligence agency suspects that the Rizian nationalist group Su Omina was behind the crime."

LineNo: 10480741,

Vina Toras: I don't understand why Cousin Rico...
en


"I don't understand why Cousin Rico would even support a group like that."

LineNo: 10481145,

Player_Romus: I appreciate the boy's efforts. Bu...
en


"I appreciate the boy's efforts. But I wish he would coordinate them with me."

LineNo: 10481247,

Player_Romus: It's true. National identity shoul...
en


"It's true. National identity should be secondary to one's loyalty to the throne."

LineNo: 10481349,

Player_Romus: That's rubbish. The monarchy and t...
en


"That's rubbish. The monarchy and the nation of Rizia cannot be separated from one another. I appreciate Rico's efforts to protect both."

LineNo: 10481451,

Player_Romus: Please don't change the subject, V...
en


"Please don't change the subject, Vina."

LineNo: 10481553,

Player_Romus: Yes, Rico has no right using the T...
en


"Yes, Rico has no right using the Toras name to serve his own xenophobic agenda."

LineNo: 10481655,

Lucita Azaro: If I may, Your Grace, why have you...
en


"If I may, Your Grace, why have you never once thrown your own weight behind Su Omina if you support its ideals?"

LineNo: 10481757,

Lucita Azaro: Agreed, Let's get back to the topi...
en


"Agreed, Let's get back to the topic at hand. Although..."

LineNo: 10481859,

Lucita Azaro: Future or not, we have no concrete...
en


"Future or not, we have no concrete proof Su Omina was behind the attack. All we have is Wehlen's word."

LineNo: 10481985,

Player_Romus: Then what are your foreign intelli...
en


"Then what are your foreign intelligence agents good for? They didn't even predict this would happen!"

LineNo: 10482087,

Player_Romus: And it's in Wehlen's interest to p...
en


"And it's in Wehlen's interest to pin the blame for the bombing on Rizia."

LineNo: 10482189,

Player_Romus: Rico has no right using the Toras...
en


"Rico has no right using the Toras name to support a xenophobic agenda."

LineNo: 10482291,

Player_Romus: I know the way these groups functi...
en


"I know the way these groups function. It's only a short leap from talk to bloodshed."

LineNo: 10482393,

Player_Romus: Without them, Wehlen's criminals w...
en


"Without them, Wehlen's criminals would be running roughshod all over our country."

LineNo: 10482495,

Player_Romus: What more do we need? It seems lik...
en


"What more do we need? It seems like a cut-and-dried case to me."

LineNo: 10482597,

Hugo Toras: That's part of the reason why I've...
en


"That's part of the reason why I've been asking you to visit Iza. Obviously the King should be kept abreast of the group's activities."

LineNo: 10482699,

Hugo Toras: Surely you don't truly feel that w...
en


"Surely you don't truly feel that way, or you wouldn't have lent your support to the group."

LineNo: 10482801,

Narrator: He smiled warmly at Vina. My daught...
en


He smiled warmly at Vina. My daughter looked away.

LineNo: 10482903,

Hugo Toras: My son is as much of a Toras as yo...
en


"My son is as much of a Toras as you or Princess Vina. And frankly, he should be commended for his efforts to protect the country from miscreants."

LineNo: 10483005,

Hugo Toras: Do you really think the Wehzek mis...
en


"Do you really think the Wehzek miscreants streaming into this country are doing so out of loyalty to you?"

LineNo: 10483107,

Lucita Azaro: They've been doing the best they c...
en


"They've been doing the best they can with their limited resources."

LineNo: 10483209,

Lucita Azaro: Exactly. We still haven't ruled ou...
en


"Exactly. We still haven't ruled out the possibility that President Smolak himself ordered it."

LineNo: 10483311,

Hugo Toras: Have you not considered the possib...
en


"Have you not considered the possibility that the attack was staged by Wehlen itself? Or another party interested in weakening both of us?"

LineNo: 10483413,

Hugo Toras: Or another party interested in wea...
en


"Or another party interested in weakening the both of us."

LineNo: 10483515,

Player_Romus: Why have we not looked into this o...
en


"Why have we not looked into this ourselves?"

LineNo: 10483617,

Lucita Azaro: With an increased foreign intellig...
en


"With an increased foreign intelligence budget, we could commission a full investigation into the Zille incident and take measures to prevent such an event from reoccurring."

LineNo: 10483743,

Lucita Azaro: Our foreign intelligence agency is...
en


"Our foreign intelligence agency is hamstrung by its limited resources, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10483845,

Titus Gordion: Pardon me, ma'am. Major. Duchess.
en


"Pardon me, ma'am. Major. Duchess."

LineNo: 10483947,

Narrator: All eyes turned towards the man in...
en


All eyes turned towards the man in the gold blazer.

LineNo: 10484049,

Titus Gordion: May I point out that you weren't p...
en


"May I point out that you weren't present on the day of the Zille incident. The King and I were."

LineNo: 10484151,

Titus Gordion: Prior to His Majesty's arrival, my...
en


"Prior to His Majesty's arrival, my men and I attempted to clear the square of every conceivable danger. However, we could not be everywhere at once."

LineNo: 10484277,

Player_Romus: What's your point, Mr. Gordion?
en


"What's your point, Mr. Gordion?"

LineNo: 10484379,

Player_Romus: You missed a bomb. That counts as...
en


"You missed a bomb. That counts as a massive lapse on the Golden Guard's part."

LineNo: 10484481,

Player_Romus: You helped save our lives back the...
en


"You helped save our lives back there. No need to make excuses."

LineNo: 10484583,

Player_Romus: It shouldn't have been your job to...
en


"It shouldn't have been your job to find the bomb. It was Wehlen's."

LineNo: 10484685,

Titus Gordion: It shouldn't have even come to tha...
en


"It shouldn't have even come to that point."

LineNo: 10484787,

Titus Gordion: Our job is to take every measure t...
en


"Our job is to take every measure to protect the King of Rizia. In that respect, we failed."

LineNo: 10484889,

Titus Gordion: Our job is to take every measure t...
en


"Our job is to take every measure to protect the King of Rizia. In that respect, we failed."

LineNo: 10484991,

Titus Gordion: This event has shown how vulnerabl...
en


"This event has shown how vulnerable you and the royal family truly are, and how ill-equipped my men and I are to seek out and neutralize threats to your safety."

LineNo: 10485093,

Titus Gordion: Therefore, it is my opinion that a...
en


"Therefore, it is my opinion that any emergency funding allocated in the wake of the Zille attack should go towards re-expanding the Golden Guard."

LineNo: 10485195,

Narrator: Lucita's jaw dropped.
en


Lucita's jaw dropped.

LineNo: 10485297,

Lucita Azaro: Captain Gordion, I trust you to gu...
en


"Captain Gordion, I trust you to guard the King, but national security is not your domain."

LineNo: 10485399,

Titus Gordion: Ma'am, back in the 1800s, the Gold...
en


"Ma'am, back in the 1800s, the Golden Guard not only protected the royal family, but was assigned to carry out special missions of national importance."

LineNo: 10485501,

Titus Gordion: This version of the Guard had the...
en


"This version of the Guard had the king's authority to conduct sensitive internal investigations without getting caught up in red tape."

LineNo: 10485603,

Player_Romus: Good point. What use are Duchess A...
en


"Good point. What use are Duchess Azaro's intelligence services if I'm not safe within my own borders?"

LineNo: 10485705,

Player_Romus: What kind of investigations did yo...
en


"What kind of investigations did you have in mind, Captain?"

LineNo: 10485807,

Player_Romus: You have enough funding, Captain G...
en


"You have enough funding, Captain Gordion. Make more efficient use of it."

LineNo: 10485909,

Player_Romus: We need to find out who's behind t...
en


"We need to find out who's behind this bombing. Can the Golden Guard help with that?"

LineNo: 10486011,

Titus Gordion: We can't carry out research in Zil...
en


"We can't carry out research in Zille. But we can work in Iza to confirm or rule out the involvement of the individuals under suspicion."

LineNo: 10486113,

Titus Gordion: If I were allowed to send men to I...
en


"If I were allowed to send men to Iza, we could confirm or rule out the involvement of the individuals under suspicion in the Zille attack."

LineNo: 10486215,

Titus Gordion: The type of investigation I'm prop...
en


"The type of investigation I'm proposing would require more, sir. I'm suggesting you allow me to send men to Iza. We can easily confirm or rule out the involvement of the individuals under suspicion in the Zille attack."

LineNo: 10486317,

Titus Gordion: With respect, sir, we don't know w...
en


"With respect, sir, we don't know whether it's a dead end. And investigating an organization with ties to the royal family is exactly the kind of sensitive mission the Golden Guard was built for."

LineNo: 10486419,

Narrator: She, Hugo and Titus glared at each...
en


She, Hugo and Titus glared at each other.

LineNo: 10486521,

Laurento Esquibel: Excuse me, Your Majesty. My fellow...
en


"Excuse me, Your Majesty. My fellow councilors. These stairs never get easier."

LineNo: 10486639,

Player_Romus: Take a moment, Mr. Esquibel.
en


"Take a moment, Mr. Esquibel."

LineNo: 10486741,

Narrator: The tension was broken by a knock o...
en


The tension was broken by a knock on the door. Laurento came in, clearly out of breath.

LineNo: 10486843,

Player_Romus: Don't interrupt us. We're in the m...
en


"Don't interrupt us. We're in the middle of an important security briefing."

LineNo: 10486945,

Player_Romus: What's going on?
en


"What's going on?"

LineNo: 10487047,

Laurento Esquibel: I understand, Your Majesty. But yo...
en


"I understand, Your Majesty. But you're going to want to hear this."

LineNo: 10487149,

Narrator: Laurento sat down. After catching h...
en


Laurento sat down. After catching his breath, he continued.

LineNo: 10487251,

Laurento Esquibel: I've just received word from Wehle...
en


"I've just received word from Wehlen's foreign minister. President Smolak plans to make it public that Rizian nationalists were involved in the Zille incident."

LineNo: 10487353,

Narrator: Lucita's hands closed into fists.
en


Lucita's hands closed into fists.

LineNo: 10487455,

Laurento Esquibel: Furthermore, given the contents of...
en


"Furthermore, given the contents of the King's speech just prior to the attack, chances are that King Romus himself will come under fire for inciting the violence."

LineNo: 10487835,

Narrator: He shook his head sadly.
en


He shook his head sadly.

LineNo: 10487937,

Laurento Esquibel: I did advise you to maintain an ai...
en


"I did advise you to maintain an air of civility, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10488063,

Player_Romus: Past is past. We have to focus on...
en


"Past is past. We have to focus on what we're going to do next."

LineNo: 10488165,

Player_Romus: Do not question my decisions, Mr....
en


"Do not question my decisions, Mr. Esquibel."

LineNo: 10488267,

Player_Romus: I didn't incite anything. I merely...
en


"I didn't incite anything. I merely told the truth."

LineNo: 10488369,

Player_Romus: I'm sorry. I must have gotten carr...
en


"I'm sorry. I must have gotten carried away."

LineNo: 10488471,

Laurento Esquibel: Our relations with Wehlen have bee...
en


"Our relations with Wehlen have been cordial enough that Smolak will not immediately blame the crown. But he will be expecting a response."

LineNo: 10488573,

Laurento Esquibel: My sincerest apologies. Let's focu...
en


"My sincerest apologies. Let's focus on how we're going to respond."

LineNo: 10488675,

Laurento Esquibel: Correct. Wehlen will be expecting...
en


"Correct. Wehlen will be expecting a response from us."

LineNo: 10488777,

Laurento Esquibel: On their own, your words might not...
en


"On their own, your words might not have been considered incendiary. But their timing was most unfortunate."

LineNo: 10488879,

Laurento Esquibel: What's done is done. But now Wehle...
en


"What's done is done. But now Wehlen will be expecting a response from us."

LineNo: 10488981,

Laurento Esquibel: Wehlen will be expecting a respons...
en


"Wehlen will be expecting a response from us."

LineNo: 10489083,

Lucita Azaro: He's just testing us. His governme...
en


"He's just testing us. His government can't prove anything."

LineNo: 10489209,

Lucita Azaro: Smolak is just testing us. His gov...
en


"Smolak is just testing us. His government can't prove anything."

LineNo: 10489311,

Hugo Toras: Still, an apology for your harsh l...
en


"Still, an apology for your harsh language would be in order so as not to inflame relations further."

LineNo: 10489437,

Player_Romus: How dare he insult us with these b...
en


"How dare he insult us with these baseless accusations?"

LineNo: 10489539,

Player_Romus: An apology won't be enough. I have...
en


"An apology won't be enough. I have to point the finger somewhere."

LineNo: 10489641,

Player_Romus: This makes me certain that Wehlen...
en


"This makes me certain that Wehlen was behind the bombing. They're trying to weaken our claim on Zille."

LineNo: 10489743,

Player_Romus: Lack of proof never stopped Wehlen...
en


"Lack of proof never stopped Wehlen from waging war on the Bluds. The Wehzeks are irrational."

LineNo: 10489845,

Player_Romus: I'll do whatever I have to do to g...
en


"I'll do whatever I have to do to get President Smolak back on our side."

LineNo: 10489947,

Lucita Azaro: That's dangerous, Your Majesty. If...
en


"That's dangerous, Your Majesty. If we begin offering concessions, there are no limits to what Wehlen will demand."

LineNo: 10490049,

Lucita Azaro: You see now why I want to launch a...
en


"You see now why I want to launch an investigation? Imagine the reaction once it comes out that Smolak attacked his own people."

LineNo: 10490151,

Hugo Toras: Yes, I can't imagine any response...
en


"Yes, I can't imagine any response that would pacify that man."

LineNo: 10490253,

Player_Romus: I understand the need to apologize...
en


"I understand the need to apologize. What I won't do is blame my own people for what happened."

LineNo: 10490355,

Player_Romus: An apology would be an admission o...
en


"An apology would be an admission of guilt. I can't do that."

LineNo: 10490457,

Player_Romus: I'll do whatever I have to do to g...
en


"I'll do whatever I have to do to get the President back on our side."

LineNo: 10490559,

Lucita Azaro: That's right. If we let Smolak bel...
en


"That's right. If we let Smolak believe we have something to apologize for, there are no limits to what he'll demand."

LineNo: 10490661,

Laurento Esquibel: People are dead, Your Majesty. Som...
en


"People are dead, Your Majesty. Someone must take the blame."

LineNo: 10490763,

Lucita Azaro: That's dangerous, Your Majesty. If...
en


"That's dangerous, Your Majesty. If we begin offering concessions, there are no limits to what Wehlen will demand."

LineNo: 10490865,

Hugo Toras: Quite right. There's no need to th...
en


"Quite right. There's no need to throw Rico to the Wehzek wolves."

LineNo: 10490967,

Lucita Azaro: Then point it right back at Wehlen...
en


"Then point it right back at Wehlen. Launch an investigation. Call Smolak's bluff."

LineNo: 10491069,

Laurento Esquibel: May I ask what the five of you wer...
en


"May I ask what the five of you were discussing before I came in?"

LineNo: 10491449,

Laurento Esquibel: May I ask what the four of you wer...
en


"May I ask what the four of you were discussing before I came in?"

LineNo: 10491551,

Hugo Toras: A question of priorities. Duchess...
en


"A question of priorities. Duchess Azaro is requesting funding for a foreign intelligence investigation into the Zille incident. Mr. Gordion would rather his Golden Guard be given funds and license to conduct its own investigations within Rizia's borders."

LineNo: 10491677,

Vina Toras: Our security response to the Zille...
en


"Our security response to the Zille incident. Duchess Azaro is requesting funds for a foreign intelligence investigation in Wehlen, while Mr. Gordion would prefer the Golden Guard be given license to investigate threats within Rizia's borders."

LineNo: 10491803,

Player_Romus: Well summarized, Vina.
en


"Well summarized, Vina."

LineNo: 10491905,

Player_Romus: Actually, taking up Titus' offer t...
en


"Actually, taking up Titus' offer to conduct a thorough investigation of Su Omina could help pacify Wehlen."

LineNo: 10492007,

Player_Romus: If I fund Duchess Azaro's investig...
en


"If I fund Duchess Azaro's investigation and it exposes Wehzek wrongdoing, Smolak won't have a leg to stand on."

LineNo: 10492109,

Hugo Toras: At the expense of Rico's dignity,...
en


"At the expense of Rico's dignity, and thus the dignity of House Toras."

LineNo: 10492211,

Titus Gordion: Rest assured that if the Duke of I...
en


"Rest assured that if the Duke of Iza has nothing to hide, his dignity will remain intact."

LineNo: 10492313,

Laurento Esquibel: A tricky needle to thread, Your Ma...
en


"A tricky needle to thread, Your Majesty. Pursuing such an investigation might lead the President to think you're undermining his authority."

LineNo: 10492415,

Vina Toras: Thank you, Your Majesty.
en


"Thank you, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10492517,

Player_Romus: Thank you for the summary, Hugo.
en


"Thank you for the summary, Hugo."

LineNo: 10492619,

Narrator: Laurento raised an eyebrow at Titus...
en


Laurento raised an eyebrow at Titus, pleasantly surprised.

LineNo: 10492721,

Player_Romus: To be honest, I'd rather not waste...
en


"To be honest, I'd rather not waste our budget on either of those."

LineNo: 10492823,

Titus Gordion: A grave mistake, Your Majesty.
en


"A grave mistake, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10492925,

Player_Romus: How much would that cost us?
en


"How much would that cost us?"

LineNo: 10493027,

Lucita Azaro: A significant portion of our emerg...
en


"A significant portion of our emergency funds. But it'll be worth it."

LineNo: 10493129,

Player_Romus: And what if it turns out Rizian na...
en


"And what if it turns out Rizian nationalists were responsible after all?"

LineNo: 10493231,

Lucita Azaro: Then they'll be found and dealt wi...
en


"Then they'll be found and dealt with."

LineNo: 10493333,

Player_Romus: More budget demands? This country...
en


"More budget demands? This country is not made of money, Duchess Azaro."

LineNo: 10493435,

Lucita Azaro: If the truth is not revealed, it w...
en


"If the truth is not revealed, it will cost us even more dearly."

LineNo: 10493537,

Player_Romus: Sounds like a good idea to me.
en


"Sounds like a good idea to me."

LineNo: 10493639,

Lucita Azaro: Then you have better judgement tha...
en


"Then you have better judgement than your father did."

LineNo: 10493741,

Lucita Azaro: For once we agree, Captain. Going...
en


"For once we agree, Captain. Going along with Wehlen's accusations without even trying to gather our own evidence would only give Smolak ammunition."

LineNo: 10493843,

Lucita Azaro: If Wehlen has nothing to hide, the...
en


"If Wehlen has nothing to hide, they will welcome our assistance."

LineNo: 10493945,

Laurento Esquibel: Showing Wehlen that you are seriou...
en


"Showing Wehlen that you are serious about investigating the potential terrorists makes diplomatic sense."

LineNo: 10494047,

Lucita Azaro: Let's not forget His Majesty has a...
en


"Let's not forget His Majesty has a personal history with the organization. Uncovering any unsavory information could harm the throne."

LineNo: 10494427,

Lucita Azaro: I agree it's dangerous to investig...
en


"I agree it's dangerous to investigate an organization that His Majesty has blood ties to."

LineNo: 10494529,

Titus Gordion: But officially clearing Su Omina's...
en


"But officially clearing Su Omina's name would be a boon for both the group and the Kingdom."

LineNo: 10494631,

Hugo Toras: Sending investigators to Zille wou...
en


"Sending investigators to Zille would also shift the focus away from Su Omina and the royal family."

LineNo: 10494733,

Hugo Toras: My pleasure. His Majesty already k...
en


"My pleasure. His Majesty already knows which course of action I'd prefer."

LineNo: 10494835,
